---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import Verify from '../../components/Verify.astro';
import Faq from '../../components/Faq.astro';
import References from '../../components/References.astro';
import LinkCard from '../../components/LinkCard.astro';
import GetMatchedCta from '../../components/GetMatchedCta.astro';

const path = '/spokane/adu-rules-spokane-valley';
const title = 'ADUs in Spokane Valley';
const description =
  'ADU rules for the City of Spokane Valley under SVMC 19.40.030: allowed types, the HB 1337 two-ADU and owner-occupancy picture, parking, impact-fee exemption, and the permit center.';

const svmc = 'https://www.codepublishing.com/WA/SpokaneValley/html/SpokaneValley19/SpokaneValley1940.html (SVMC 19.40.030)';

const faqItems = [
  {
    q: 'Does Spokane Valley have its own ADU rules?',
    a: 'Yes. The City of Spokane Valley is a separate jurisdiction with its own municipal code (SVMC 19.40.030) and permit center. Its ADU rules can differ from the City of Spokane and from unincorporated Spokane County, so confirm the Spokane Valley standards if your lot is inside the city.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is owner occupancy required for a Spokane Valley ADU?',
    a: 'The published SVMC still contains an owner-occupancy provision adopted before HB 1337. Because Spokane Valley is in an urban growth area, HB 1337 generally prohibits owner-occupancy requirements, so that older provision is likely preempted. Confirm the current status with the city before relying on it either way.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does Spokane Valley charge impact fees on an ADU?',
    a: 'Spokane Valley exempts ADUs from impact fees. Other permit and connection fees still apply, set by the city fee schedule. Confirm the current schedule with the permit center.',
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path={path}>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Spokane rules', href: '/spokane' }, { label: 'Spokane Valley', href: path }]} />
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Jurisdiction"
    title="ADUs in Spokane Valley"
    lede="These rules apply to lots inside the City of Spokane Valley, a separate jurisdiction from the City of Spokane and unincorporated Spokane County. ADUs are governed by SVMC 19.40.030. Spokane Valley is in an urban growth area, so HB 1337 applies and some older code language is likely superseded."
    cta={{ href: '/get-matched', label: 'Get matched with a builder' }}
    secondary={{ href: '/guides/can-i-build-an-adu-spokane', label: 'Can I build an ADU?' }}
  />

  <section class="container-prose rich-text pb-2">
    <h2>Spokane Valley is its own jurisdiction</h2>
    <p>
      Spokane Valley does not follow the City of Spokane code or the unincorporated county code. If
      your parcel is inside Spokane Valley city limits, the Spokane Valley Municipal Code (SVMC
      19.40.030) and the city permit center are your sources. Because the city is in an urban growth
      area, HB 1337 applies, and older provisions that conflict with it are likely preempted.
    </p>

    <h2>The HB 1337 stale-language flag</h2>
    <p>
      The published SVMC still shows an owner-occupancy requirement (the owner must occupy the primary
      dwelling or the ADU for six or more months per year, with a recorded deed restriction), adopted
      under Ordinance 21-010 in 2021. That language predates HB 1337, which prohibits owner-occupancy
      requirements inside a UGA, so it is likely no longer enforceable. Whether the city has formally
      adopted its HB 1337 update is being confirmed, so do not plan around an owner-occupancy
      requirement without checking with the city first.
    </p>

    <h2>Spokane Valley ADU rules at a glance</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Rule</th><th>Current Spokane Valley standard</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Allowed ADU types</td>
          <td>Attached and detached ADUs, in zones that permit single-family dwellings (SVMC 19.40.030).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Maximum ADUs per lot</td>
          <td>At least two per lot are required inside the UGA under HB 1337. Whether the SVMC has adopted that: <Verify item="whether SVMC 19.40.030 has been updated to allow two ADUs per lot" source={svmc} /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Maximum ADU size</td>
          <td>At least 1,000 sq ft must be allowed under HB 1337 (older 50 percent and 300 sq ft figures predate it). Exact current figure: <Verify item="the current maximum ADU size in SVMC 19.40.030" source={svmc} /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Maximum height</td>
          <td><Verify item="the maximum ADU height in the SVMC (at least 24 ft must be allowed under HB 1337)" source={svmc} /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Setbacks</td>
          <td><Verify item="ADU setbacks, which follow the underlying zone dimensions in SVMC 19.70" source={svmc} /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Off-street parking</td>
          <td><Verify item="the current ADU parking requirement in SVMC 19.40.030 (reported as one space; HB 1337 limits parking near major transit)" source={svmc} /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Owner-occupancy</td>
          <td>Older SVMC language requires it, but that predates HB 1337 and is likely preempted inside the UGA. Current status: <Verify item="whether Spokane Valley still enforces owner-occupancy or has removed it to comply with HB 1337" source={svmc} /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Impact fees</td>
          <td>Spokane Valley exempts ADUs from impact fees.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Permit fees</td>
          <td><Verify item="current Spokane Valley ADU permit fees on the city master fee schedule" source="https://www.spokanevalleywa.gov/242/Residential-Building-Permits" /></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>The permit process in Spokane Valley</h2>
    <p>
      ADU permitting runs through the Spokane Valley permit center, which reviews zoning and building
      requirements and issues permits. Confirm the current submittal checklist, review timeline, and
      fees with the city. Our homeowner permit guide explains what to expect.
    </p>
  </section>

  <Faq items={faqItems} heading="Spokane Valley ADU questions" />

  <References
    sources={[
      { label: 'Spokane Valley Municipal Code 19.40.030, Accessory Dwelling Units (codepublishing.com)', href: 'https://www.codepublishing.com/WA/SpokaneValley/html/SpokaneValley19/SpokaneValley1940.html', note: 'Types, count, size, parking, owner-occupancy.' },
      { label: 'City of Spokane Valley residential building permits (spokanevalleywa.gov)', href: 'https://www.spokanevalleywa.gov/242/Residential-Building-Permits', note: 'Permit center and master fee schedule.' },
      { label: 'RCW 36.70A.681 (app.leg.wa.gov)', href: 'https://app.leg.wa.gov/RCW/default.aspx?cite=36.70A.681', note: 'HB 1337 ADU requirements that preempt conflicting local rules.' },
    ]}
  />

  <section class="container-page py-8">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold">Related</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <LinkCard href="/guides/adu-permits-spokane" eyebrow="Guide" title="ADU Permits in Spokane" blurb="The homeowner walkthrough of the permit process." />
      <LinkCard href="/guides/adu-cost-spokane" eyebrow="Guide" title="ADU Cost in Spokane" blurb="Dated cost ranges with basis." />
      <LinkCard href="/guides/hb-1337-spokane" eyebrow="Guide" title="HB 1337 Explained" blurb="The state law behind these rules." />
    </div>
  </section>

  <GetMatchedCta />
</BaseLayout>
